The basis usage of l2_firewall module
-------------------------------------

1. Launch a single switch 3 node mininet topology

2. Launch the l2_firewall by
   pox log.level --DEBUG l2_firewall --firewall-file="xxxx"
   For example,  pox log.level --DEBUG l2_firewall --firewall-file="cs589.firewall.rules"

3. The firewall file contains the port MAC addresses that are ALLOWED in the firewall. 
   Empty firewall rules are permitted for testing purpose. It means no traffic is allowed

4. To test in mininet, do "pingall"


